# 2. Load Data Files ð
# --------------------------------------------------------
# Load the main data frame for analysis from an RDS file
df <-readRDS("/Users/jeremygenette_studio/Documents/Research/Code/IF0_babbling_lexical/Data/df_vf_for_analysis.rds")

# Load a supplementary data frame containing Child Babbling Ratio (CBR) data

df_CBR <-readRDS("/Users/jeremygenette_studio/Documents/Research/Code/IF0_babbling_lexical/Data/df_CBR.rds")

# 3. Round Numeric Columns in the Main Data Frame ð¢
# --------------------------------------------------------
# Round numeric columns to 3 decimal places, leaving other columns unchanged
df_RQ3 <- as.data.frame(lapply(df, function(x) if (is.numeric(x)) round(x, 3) else x))

# 4. Merge Data Frames ð
# --------------------------------------------------------
# Merge the main data frame with the CBR data frame by "CHILD" and "AGE"
df_RQ3 <- left_join(df_RQ3, df_CBR, by = c("CHILD", "AGE"))

# 5. Create "frontness" Column (Vowel Frontness) ð¤
# --------------------------------------------------------
# Assign vowel frontness based on the first character of the "vwl_nucl" column
df_RQ3$frt[df_RQ3$vwl_nucl %in% c("A", "u", "<")] <- "back"
df_RQ3$frt[df_RQ3$vwl_nucl %in% c("i", "a")] <- "front"

# Rename CHILD column with unique anonymous identifiers
if ("CHILD" %in% colnames(df_RQ3)) {
  df_RQ3$CHILD <- factor(df_RQ3$CHILD)  # Ensure it's a factor
  levels(df_RQ3$CHILD) <- paste("Child", seq_along(levels(df_RQ3$CHILD)))  # Rename levels
}


# Convert the "frontness" column to a factor
df_RQ3$frontness <- as.factor(df_RQ3$frt)

# 6. Filter, Transform, and Tidy the Data ð ï¸
# --------------------------------------------------------
df_RQ3 <- df_RQ3 %>%
  filter(type == "lexical") %>%           # Retain only "prelexical" type rows
  group_by(CHILD) %>%                        # Group by "CHILD" for scaling
  mutate(
    item = as.factor(item),                 # Convert "item" to a factor
    hgt = as.factor(hgt),                   # Convert "hgt" (height) to a factor
    frt = as.factor(frontness),             # Convert "frontness" to a factor
    CHILD = as.factor(CHILD),               # Convert "CHILD" to a factor
    cumvoc = log(cumvoc),
    period = ifelse(AGE_ctrd <= 0, "prelexical", "lexical") # Define "period" based on CBR values
  ) %>%
  ungroup()  %>%
  select(
    -c(item, ID_vwl, type, F1_F0_distance, F0, F1, first_word, F1_F0_distance, frontness,frt)
  )  # Drop unnecessary columns

contrasts(df_RQ3$hgt) <- contr.sum(levels(df_RQ3$hgt))
df_RQ3$hgt <- relevel(df_RQ3$hgt, ref = "low")


# 7. Final Output Preview ð
# --------------------------------------------------------
# Print the first few rows of the preprocessed data frame
print(head(df_RQ3))
NA

3. Statistical Modelling ð

Model 1: Intercept-only Model

m1 <- glmer(
  data = df_RQ3, 
  formula = hgt ~ 1 + (1 | CHILD), 
  family = binomial(link = "logit"), 
  control = glmerControl(optimizer = "bobyqa", optCtrl = list(maxfun = 2000000))
)

saveRDS(m1, file = "models/m1_intercept_only_RQ3.rds")

Model 2: Fixed Effect of F1

m2_fixed_F1 <- glmer(
  data = df_RQ3, 
  formula = hgt ~ F1_Regression_Normalized + (1 | CHILD), 
  family = binomial(link = "logit"), 
  control = glmerControl(optimizer = "bobyqa", optCtrl = list(maxfun = 10000000))
)

saveRDS(m2_fixed_F1, file = "models/m2_F1_fixed_effect_RQ3.rds")
anova_results_m2 <- anova(m1, m2_fixed_F1)

# Define color palettes
F1_color <- c("#9F3400", "#FF681F", "#FFBE9F")

# Define a function for plotting
create_plot <- function(model, term1, term2, colors, y_label, x_label, legend_title) {
  plot <- plot_model(model, type = "pred", terms = c("cumvoc [all]", term2, term1), pred.type = "fe") +
    labs(
      color = legend_title,
      y = y_label,
      x = x_label,
      title = ""
    ) +
    theme_cowplot() +
    scale_color_manual(values = colors) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = colors) +
    scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::percent_format(), limits = c(0, 1)) +
    theme(legend.position = "bottom", legend.box = "horizontal")
  return(plot)
}
